<p>Return of boolean literal statements wrapped into <code>if-then-else</code> flow should be simplified.</p>
<p>Note that if the result of the expression is not a boolean but for instance an integer, then double negation should be used for proper
conversion.</p>
<pre>
if (expression) {
  return true;
} else {
  return false;
}
</pre>
<p>or</p>
<pre>
if (expression) {
  return true;
}
return false;
</pre>
<h2>Compliant Solution</h2>
<pre>
return expression;
</pre>
<p>or</p>
<pre>
return !!expression;
</pre>